In the MATTER OF Sue A. WEINTRAUB for the Appointment of a Guardian of the Property No. 44, Sept. Term, 2017 Court of Appeals of Maryland. January 10, 2018 Argued by Edward P. Parent (Steven D. Silverman and Jamie Lee, Silverman Thompson Slutkin White LLC of Baltimore, MD), on brief for Petitioner. Argued by Ria P. Rochvarg (Ria P. Rochvarg, P.A. of Ellicott City, MD), on brief for Respondent. Argued before: Barbera, C.J., Greene, Adkins, McDonald, Watts, Hotten, Getty, JJ. PER CURIAM ORDER

The petition for writ of certiorari in the above-entitled case having been granted and argued, it is this 10th day of January, 2018,

ORDERED, by the Court of Appeals of Maryland, that the writ of certiorari be, and it is hereby, dismissed with costs, the petition having been improvidently granted.
